The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Confident Bengal open vs Tripura today

 - EAST ZONE ONE-DAYERS 

 Sourashish Lahiri and Rohan Gavaskar during practice in Dhanbad on Friday. Picture by Gautam Dey 

Dhanbad: Though defending champions Bengal will miss key man former India captain Sourav Ganguly for Saturdays match, skipper Deep Dasgupta said the team was confident to take on Tripura in the opening of the East Zone one-day round-robin meet here. 

We are confident and will put up good show, Deep said after having net practice here. Sourav, who is expected to join the squad on Sunday, will be available for the rest of the matches. 

Rahman, an organiser of the Dhanbad Cricket Association said in anticipation of Souravs presence, 70 percent of tickets have been sold. According to sources in the team, Bengal may leave out Arindam Das and Kamal Hassan Mondal from the final XII. Subhajit Paul is likely to be the super-sub. 

The hosts Jharkhand will take on Orissa in another match here tomorrow. 

Besides Bengal, the other East Zone teams, which would vie for honours are Tripura, Assam, Orissa and Jharkhand. Jharkhand would miss local hero Mahendra Singh Dhoni who is now on national duty in Pakistan. 

Bengal team (likely): Subhamoy Das, Sanjib Sanyal, Avishek Jhunjhunwala, Rohan Gavaskar, Deep Dasgupta (captain), Laxmi Ratan Shukla, Manoj Tewari, Sourashish Lahiri, Shiv Sagar Singh, Ranadeb Bose, Shib Shankar Paul. Super sub: Subhajit Paul. 

